From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rachapalli Bandi Jagadeesh <jagadeesh.rachapalli.bandi@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 3 Feb 2026 22:48:34 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Fix module symbols import issue

xe-vfio-pci driver use the symbols which are exported by xe driver.
Since symbols are not imported from xe driver, observing below errors.
To fix these errors, imported xe-vfio-pci symbols from xe driver.

Errors:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
ERROR: modpost: module xe-vfio-pci uses symbol xe_sriov_vfio_stop_copy_enter
from namespace module:xe-vfio-pci, but does not import it.
ERROR: modpost: module xe-vfio-pci uses symbol xe_sriov_vfio_stop_copy_exit
from namespace module:xe-vfio-pci, but does not import it.
ERROR: modpost: module xe-vfio-pci uses symbol xe_sriov_vfio_suspend_device
from namespace module:xe-vfio-pci, but does not import it.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

V1: Fix MODULE_IMPORT_NS for xe-vfio-pci namespace against rhel 10.1 [Raju]

Error:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
error: expected ',' or ';' before 'xe' MODULE_IMPORT_NS(xe-vfio-pci);
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Reviewed-by: S A Muqthyar Ahmed <syed.abdul.muqthyar.ahmed@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Rachapalli Bandi Jagadeesh <jagadeesh.rachapalli.bandi@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Kanaka Raju Nayana <kanaka.raju.nayana@intel.com>
---
 drivers/vfio/pci/xe/main.c | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/vfio/pci/xe/main.c b/drivers/vfio/pci/xe/main.c
index 115de55..acc02fd 100644
--- a/drivers/vfio/pci/xe/main.c
+++ b/drivers/vfio/pci/xe/main.c
@@ -568,3 +568,10 @@ module_pci_driver(xe_vfio_pci_driver);
 MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");
 MODULE_AUTHOR("Michał Winiarski <michal.winiarski@intel.com>");
 MODULE_DESCRIPTION("VFIO PCI driver with migration support for Intel Graphics");
+#ifdef BPM_MODULE_IMPORT_TO_STRING_LITERAL_PRESENT
+MODULE_IMPORT_NS(xe-vfio-pci);
+#else
+#ifdef BPM_EXPORT_SYMBOL_FOR_MODULES_NOT_PRESENT
+MODULE_IMPORT_NS("xe-vfio-pci");
+#endif
+#endif
-- 
